etymologies: late 17th century; earliest use found in Francis Willughby (1635–1672), naturalist. Origin unknown. Perhaps compare Older Scots poch, potch, Scots poach, potch denoting the same fish

definitions: Any of various small, spiny marine fishes of the family Agonidae; = "poacher"; especially the armed bullhead, Agonus cataphractus, of coastal waters of northern Europe.
